    {
      "type": "action",
      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Cinder Lung",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>Any breathing creature bitten by a cinder ghoul begins to have their lungs filled with smoke and cinder.</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:fortitude|dc:26]</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 1} and [[/r {1d6}[fire]]]{1d6 fire damage} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 2} and [[/r {2d6}[fire]]]{2d6 fire damage} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Drained]{Drained 3} and [[/r {3d6}[fire]]]{3d6 fire damage} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> suffocating and cannot reduce below stage 4 until the smoke is purged; purging the smoke requires a successful @Check[type:medicine|dc:26] check to Administer First Aid (which stops the creature from suffocating and returns the creature to stage 3; stage 2 on a critical success) or a magical effect that removes curses or the drained condition (which stops the creature from suffocating and ends the curse). If the creature dies from suffocation, it rises as a cinder ghoul the next midnight.</p>"
        },
        "source": {
          "value": ""
        },
        "traits": {
          "value": [
            "curse",
            "fire",
            "necromancy"
          ],
          "rarity": "common",
